Logs Explorer filters
1) Namespace (zone) creation attempts (including denied)

Use Admin Activity and filter by Service Directory + CreateNamespace:

logName=~"cloudaudit.googleapis.com%2Factivity"
protoPayload.serviceName="servicedirectory.googleapis.com"
protoPayload.methodName="google.cloud.servicedirectory.v1.RegistrationService.CreateNamespace"


Now add “403-ish” failures:

protoPayload.status.code=7


status.code=7 = PERMISSION_DENIED (commonly what you think of as HTTP 403 in these logs)

Who did it: protoPayload.authenticationInfo.principalEmail

What they tried to create: look in protoPayload.request / resourceName

Service name + method name are documented here.

2) “Records” creation attempts (Service + Endpoint)

If the user is creating a namespace and then adding entries, you’ll usually see one or more of these methods:

logName=~"cloudaudit.googleapis.com%2Factivity"
protoPayload.serviceName="servicedirectory.googleapis.com"
(
  protoPayload.methodName="google.cloud.servicedirectory.v1.RegistrationService.CreateService"
  OR protoPayload.methodName="google.cloud.servicedirectory.v1.RegistrationService.CreateEndpoint"
)


Add denied filter if needed:

protoPayload.status.code=7


(Those method names are in the Service Directory audit logging doc.)

3) If you’re not sure which SD method they hit

Broad catch-all:

protoPayload.serviceName="servicedirectory.googleapis.com"
protoPayload.status.code=7


Then expand an entry and look at:

protoPayload.methodName

protoPayload.authorizationInfo.permission (what permission was checked)

protoPayload.resourceName (the SD resource path)
